n%20soldier%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Russian%20APCs%20%26quot%3Bare%20easy%20to%20destroy%20but%20not%20good%20to%20fight%20directly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium-caliber%20cannon%20can%20engage%20infantry%20from%20a%20distance%20or%20even%20damage%20a%20tank%20%E2%80%94%20both%20of%20which%20are%20uses%20observed%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20is%20apparent%20that%20infantry%20formations%20fare%20poorly%20against%20cannons%20if%20they%20are%20not%20supported%2C%26quot%3B%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20also%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20urban%20warfare%20as%20they%20are%20capable%20of%20suppressing%20positions%20from%20ranges%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20beyond%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20standard%20shoulder-fired%20anti-armor%20weapons%20carried%20by%20infantry%20formations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20BMP-2%20armored%20amphibious%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525c20955f52b01b35bb3ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPersonnel%20load%20the%20gun%20of%20a%20BMP-2%20amphibious%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%20during%20an%20arms%20exhibition%20Russia%20in%20September%202013.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FSergei%20Karpukhin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20instinctively%20view%20the%20biggest%20cannon%20as%20the%20best%20in%20terms%20of%20firepower%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20that%20straightforward.%20A%20main%20battle%20tank%20like%20the%20US-made%20M-1%20or%20the%20Soviet-designed%20T-72%20are%20armed%20with%20120-mm%20or%20125-mm%20guns%20that%20can%20destroy%20other%20tanks%20from%20miles%20away.%20But%20those%20tanks%20carry%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20cannon%20rounds%20and%20their%20main%20guns%20have%20a%20limited%20rate%20of%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20their%20main%20guns%20are%20ill-suited%20for%20many%20targets%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20During%20World%20War%20II%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fww2armor%2Fposts%2Fnow-hear-thiswhat-main-gun-ammunition-was-carried-by-the-m4-sherman-tanks-with-t%2F328151730865334%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20targets%20engaged%20by%20the%20M4%20Sherman%20tank%20were%20soft%20targets%20such%20as%20infantry%2C%20anti-tank%20guns%2C%20and%20bunkers.%20To%20send%20tanks%20after%20dispersed%20targets%20like%20infantry%20is%20like%20hunting%20rabbits%20with%20a%20howitzer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20tanks%20have%20machine%20guns%20in%20the%2012.7-mm%20and%207.62-mm%20range%2C%20to%20engage%20personnel%20or%20to%20hit%20soft%20vehicles%2C%20such%20as%20trucks%2C%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20big%20cannon%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium-caliber%2C%20rapid-fire%20cannon%2C%20such%20as%20the%20M242%20Bushmaster%2025-mm%20chain%20gun%20on%20the%20US's%20M2%20Bradley%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%2C%20combine%20a%20rate%20of%20fire%20like%20that%20of%20a%20machine%20gun%20with%20the%20heavier%20shells%20used%20by%20a%20cannon.%20The%202A42%20can%20pump%20out%20up%20500%20rounds%20a%20minute%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-tulamash-ru.translate.goog%2Fcatalog%2F15%3F_x_tr_sl%3Dauto%26_x_tr_tl%3Den%26_x_tr_hl%3Den-US%26_x_tr_sch%3Dhttp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E27A2%3C%2Fa%3E%20model%20can%20shoot%20330%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20Bradley%20armored%20Fighting%20vehicle%20M240%20machine%20gun%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6525b9b86561dd877e76af3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20fire%20the%20M240C%20coaxial%20machine%20gun%20on%20a%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%20during%20an%20exercise%20in%20Lithuania%20in%20November%202014.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Keith%20Anderson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20weapons%20can%20also%20fire%20a%20variety%20of%20ammunition%2C%20including%20armor-piercing%20and%20high-explosive%20rounds.%20The%20M242%20Bushmaster%20can%20even%20fire%20depleted-uranium%20shells%20against%20tanks.%20Bradleys%20famously%20used%20their%2025-mm%20guns%20to%20suppress%20Iraqi%20T-72%20tanks%2C%20buying%20them%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoffeeordie.com%2Fbradley-headed-to-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edestroy%20the%20Iraqi%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20M2's%20TOW%20anti-tank%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20if%20they%20have%20a%20choice%2C%20should%20pick%20a%20fight%20with%20heavily%20armored%20tanks%2C%20but%20medium%20cannon%20have%20proven%20their%20value.%20Britain%20found%2030-mm%20cannon%20useful%20in%20the%20Falklands%2C%20Cranny-Evans%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20these%20weapons%20%26quot%3Bwere%20also%20used%20as%20a%20form%20of%20precision%20direct%20fire%20in%20Afghanistan%20where%20they%20served%20to%20quickly%20suppress%20Taliban%20forces%2C%20and%20similar%20outcomes%20have%20been%20reported%20by%20French%20forces%20fighting%20in%20Mali.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20common%20for%20infantry%20fighting%20and%20reconnaissance%20vehicles%20to%20carry%20guns%20that%20would%20have%20been%20the%20main%20armament%20of%20tanks%20in%20the%20early%20years%20of%20World%20War%20II.%20Future%20vehicles%20will%20still%20probably%20be%20armed%20with%20medium%20cannon%2C%20though%20with%20some%20innovations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20M2A3%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65259cf868f1d46f52ad8f1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20M2A3%20Bradley%20Fighting%20Vehicle%20at%20a%20range%20in