alUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fanalysis-israel-hamas-war-upends-bidens-two-pronged-middle-east-strategy%2Farticleshow%2F104323036.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fanalysis-israel-hamas-war-upends-bidens-two-pronged-middle-east-strategy%2Famp_articleshow%2F104323036.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fanalysis-israel-hamas-war-upends-bidens-two-pronged-middle-east-strategy%2Famp_articleshow%2F104323036.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20Loses%20Bid%20To%20Regain%20Seat%20On%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20on%20Tuesday%20rejected%20a%20bid%20by%20Russia%20to%20regain%20a%20seat%20on%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Council%2C%20from%20which%20it%20was%20ousted%20after%20invading%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20which%20was%20competing%20with%20Bulgaria%20and%20Albania%20for%20two%20open%20spots%20allocated%20to%20the%20Eastern%20Europe%20regional%20group%2C%20nonetheless%20received%2083%20votes%20in%20its%20favor%20from%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly's%20193%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20for%20the%20body's%202024-2026%20term%20had%20been%20viewed%20as%20a%20test%20of%20what%20Moscow%20contended%20was%20quiet%20support%20despite%20fierce%20Western-led%20criticism%20over%20its%20brutal%20assault%20on%20its%20neighbor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20vote%20comes%20just%20days%20after%20a%20Russian%20missile%20attack%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20village%20of%20Groza%20killed%20more%20than%2050%20people%2C%20although%20global%20attention%20has%20since%20turned%20to%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestinian%20militants%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUN%20member%20states%20sent%20a%20strong%20signal%20to%20Russia's%20leadership%20that%20a%20government%20responsible%20for%20countless%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity%20doesn't%20belong%20on%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Council%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Louis%20Charbonneau%20of%20international%20NGO%20Human%20Rights%20Watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlbanian%20ambassador%20Ferit%20Hoxha%2C%20whose%20country%20received%20123%20votes%20while%20Bulgaria%20received%20160%2C%20had%20said%20earlier%20that%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20%26quot%3Bhas%20an%20important%20choice%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrate%20that%20it%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20take%20an%20arsonist%20for%20a%20firefighter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Human%20Rights%20Council's%2047%20members%20are%20allocated%20by%20region%2C%20and%20each%20large%20regional%20group%20usually%20pre-selects%20its%20own%20candidates%2C%20which%20the%20General%20Assembly%20then%20typically%20approves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20year%2C%20two%20groups%20had%20more%20candidates%20than%20available%20seats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Latin%20America%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Cuba%2C%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%20and%20Peru%20were%20vying%20for%20three%20seats%2C%20and%20in%20Eastern%20Europe%2C%20Albania%2C%20Bulgaria%20and%20Russia%20sought%20two%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20vote%20takes%20place%20by%20secret%20ballot%2C%20testing%20Russia's%20contention%20that%20it%20has%20private%20support%20in%20developing%20countries%20weary%20of%20the%20West's%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20support%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202022%2C%2093%20countries%20voted%20to%20suspend%20Russia%20from%20the%20council%2C%20while%2024%20opposed%20that%20punishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20vote%20against%20Russia%20was%20less%20lopsided%20than%20other%20resolutions%20defending%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20drew%20approval%20from%20around%20140%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVotes%20for%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20are%20more%20complicated%20as%20some%20countries%20whose%20own%20records%20face%20scrutiny%20are%20uneasy%20about%20authorizing%20repercussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E-%20'Undermine%20credibility'%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20often%20criticized%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20over%20its%20membership%20and%20alleged%20slant%20against%20Israel%2C%20although%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20rejoined%20the%20group%20after%20a%20pullout%20by%20his%20predecessor%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia's%20reelection%20to%20that%20body%2C%20while%20it%20openly%20continues%20to%20commit%20war%20crimes%20and%20other%20atrocities%2C%20would%20be%20an%20ugly%20stain%20that%20would%20undermine%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20institution%20and%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%26quot%3B%20senior%20US%20diplomat%20Robert%20Wood%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Vassily%20Nebenzia%2C%20the%20Russian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20insisted%20that%20there%20%26quot%3Bare%20no%20beacons%20of%20democracy%20or%20rogue%20states%2C%20as%20is%20sometimes%20being%20portrayed.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20member-state%20can%20claim%20to%20be%20immune%20from%20human%20rights%20violations.%20But%20the%20solution%20is%20to%20strengthen%20international%20regulation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERichard%20Gowan%2C%20who%20follows%20the%20United%20Nations%20for%20the%20International%20Crisis%20Group%2C%20said%20that%20Western%20diplomats%20were%20worried%20that%20Russia%20could%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20has%20always%20argued%20that%20many%20UN%20members%20sympathize%20with%20it%20in%20private%20but%20won't%20support%20it%20in%20public%20for%20fear%20of%20antagonizing%20Western%20powers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BMoscow%20will%20hope%20that%20this%20supposed%20silent%20majority%20supports%20it%20in%20this%20secret%20vote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocacy%20group%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20had%20called%20on%20countries%20to%20oppose%20the%20candidacies%20of%20Russia%2C%20China%20and%20Cuba.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20at%20least%2C%20faced%20little%20risk%20as%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20four%20countries%20in%20the%20Asian%20group%20vying%20for%20four%20open%20seats%2C%20alongside%20Japan%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20Kuwait.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20and%20several%20other%20Western%20governments%20say%20China%20is%20committing%20genocide%20against%20its%20mostly%20Muslim%20Uyghur%20minority%20through%20massive%20camps%2C%20a%20charge%20denied%20by%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20was%20ultimately%20reelected%20with%20154%20votes%20while%20Cuba%20also%20retained%20its%20seat%20with%20146%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696956180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fuunod0bo_putin-to-china-_625x300_12_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-loses-bid-to-regain-seat-on-un-human-rights-council-4469079%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20on%20Tuesday%20rejected%20a%20bid%20by%20Russia%20to%20regain%20a%20seat%20on%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Council%2C%20from%20which%20it%20was%20ousted%20after%20invading%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-loses-bid-to-regain-seat-on-un-human-rights-council-4469079%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-loses-bid-to-regain-seat-on-un-human-rights-council-4469079%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-loses-bid-to-regain-seat-on-un-human-rights-council-4469079%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20say%20Israeli%20bombardment%20feels%20like%20new%20'Nakba'%22%2C%2