0to%20cleaner%20energy%20sources%20such%20as%20solar%20and%20wind%20power%2C%20more%20than%204%20lakh%20workers%20in%20the%20coal%20industry%20will%20lose%20their%20jobs%20by%202050%2C%20a%20report%20released%20by%20the%20Global%20Energy%20Monitor%20on%20October%2010%20says.%20Workers%20in%20China%20and%20India%20will%20be%20hardest%20hit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20report%20predicts%20that%20Coal%20India%20will%20cut%20down%20on%20more%20than%2070%2C000%20jobs%20by%20then.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20throws%20light%20on%20how%20crucial%20a%20just%20transition%20to%20clean%20energy%20will%20be%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECoal%20jobs%20to%20be%20hit%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDecarbonisation%20%E2%80%93%20reducing%20the%20carbon%20emissions%20produced%20by%20human%20activities%20such%20as%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20is%20one%20of%20the%20main%20techniques%20advocated%20to%20keep%20global%20warming%20below%20specific%20levels%20so%20as%20to%20reduce%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20(such%20as%20heat%20waves%2C%20intense%20rainfall%20and%20other%20extreme%20weather%20events)%20worldwide.%20One%20means%20of%20decarbonisation%20is%20to%20shift%20to%20cleaner%20forms%20of%20energy%2C%20such%20as%20solar%20and%20wind%20power%2C%20and%20decrease%20coal%20production%20by%20shutting%20down%20existing%20mines.%20But%20what%20of%20the%20coal%20mines%20that%20have%20to%20close%20down%3F%20The%20coal%20industry%20is%20a%20crucial%20source%20of%20livelihood%2C%20especially%20in%20rural%20areas%20in%20developing%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Global%20Energy%20Monitor%2C%20a%20US-based%20NGO%20that%20compiles%20and%20publishes%20information%20on%20clean%20energy%20worldwide%20%E2%80%93%20including%20transitioning%20to%20such%20energy%20sources%2C%20compiled%20data%20on%20employment%20at%204%2C300%20active%20and%20proposed%20coal%20mines%20and%20projects%20around%20the%20world%20that%20are%20cumulatively%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20global%20coal%20production.%20This%20was%20done%20through%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalenergymonitor.org%2Fprojects%2Fglobal-coal-mine-tracker%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20Coal%20Mine%20Tracker%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20analysis%20included%20data%20from%20mines%20in%2070%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20which%20has%20an%20estimated%203.3%20lakh%20workers%20in%20coal%20mines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20finds%20that%20nearly%2027%20lakh%20coal%20miners%20produce%2093%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20coal%2C%20with%20the%20vast%20majority%20working%20in%20Asia%20(around%2022%20lakh%20jobs).%20By%202050%2C%20around%209.9%20lakh%20coal%20mine%20jobs%20will%20no%20longer%20exist%20due%20to%20the%20closure%20of%20mines%20across%20the%20world.%20Over%20one-third%20of%20the%20existing%20workforce%20will%20face%20layoffs%2C%20even%20without%20climate%20pledges%20or%20policies%20to%20phase%20out%20coal.%20Currently%2C%204%2C14%2C200%20workers%20operate%20mines%20that%20may%20reach%20their%20end%20of%20operation%20before%202035.%20So%20the%20layoffs%20by%202035%20will%20affect%20on%20average%20100%20workers%20per%20day%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20them%20are%20in%20Asia%20alone.%20The%20Global%20Energy%20Monitor%20report%20estimates%20that%20China%20and%20India%20will%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20layoffs%20as%20coal%20mines%20are%20closed%20down.%20China%20has%20more%20than%201.5%20million%20coal%20miners%20who%20produce%20over%2085%25%20of%20its%20coal%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20half%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20output.%20India%20is%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20second-largest%20coal%20producer%20after%20China%20and%20the%20state-owned%20Coal%20India%20will%20face%20the%20most%20potential%20layoffs%20by%202050%3A%20an%20estimated%2073%2C800%20direct%20workers%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20finds%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20mines%20expected%20to%20close%20in%20the%20coming%20decades%20have%20no%20planning%20underway%20to%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20those%20operations%20or%20manage%20a%20transition%20to%20a%20post-coal%20economy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F09%2F182619562_00d6f703b6_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20coal%20mine%20at%20an%20unspecified%20location%20in%20India.%20Credit%3A%20Nitin%20Kirloskar%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F09%2F182619562_00d6f703b6_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F09%2F182619562_00d6f703b6_b-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-9811%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20coal%20mine%20at%20an%20unspecified%20location%20in%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Nitin%20Kirloskar%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Regional%20balances%20are%20crucial%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20coal%20industry%20has%20a%20long%20list%20of%20mines%20that%20will%20close%20in%20the%20near%20term%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20them%20state-owned%20enterprises%20with%20a%20government%20stake%2C%E2%80%9D%20commented%20researcher%20Tiffany%20Means%2C%20one%20of%20the%20co-authors%20of%20the%20Global%20Energy%20Monitor%20report.%20%E2%80%9CGovernments%20need%20to%20shoulder%20their%20share%20of%20the%20burden%20to%20ensure%20a%20managed%20transition%20for%20those%20workers%20and%20communities%20as%20we%20move%20into%20a%20clean%20energy%20economy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%E2%80%9Cjust%E2%80%9D%20transition%20involves%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20ensuring%20the%20rehabilitation%20of%20workers%20who%20have%20lost%20their%20jobs.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fglobal%2Ftopics%2Fgreen-jobs%2FWCMS_824102%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520Just%2520Transition%2520involves%2520maximizing%2Cfundamental%2520labour%2520principles%2520and%2520rights%2520.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20just%20transition%20is%20about%20%E2%80%9Cgreening%20the%20economy%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20as%20fair%20and%20inclusive%20as%20possible%20to%20everyone%20concerned%2C%20creating%20decent%20work%20opportunities%20and%20leaving%20no%20one%20behind%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findia-just-transition-plans-coal%2F%5C%22%3ELife%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Oldest%20Coal%20Belt%20Shows%20Why%20Plans%20for%20Transition%20Must%20Begin%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20wakeup%20call%20to%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20problem%20at%20hand%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20Runa%20Sarkar%2C%20professor%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%20Calcutta.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20coal%20mining%20region%20most%20affected%20by%20mine%20closure%20is%20West%20Bengal%20in%20India.%20Further%2C%20for%20every%20worker%20affected%20in%20the%20formal%20economy%2C%20at%20least%20four%20others%20are%20affected%20in%20the%20informal%20sector%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sarkar%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20however%2C%20coal%20production%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20country%2C%20with%20talks%20of%20reopening%20some%20closed%20mines%20to%20meet%20current%20demand%2C%20she%20added.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20in%20October%202022%20also%20issued%20fresh%20guidelines%20on%20mine%20closure%20taking%20into%20account%20its%20associated%20ecological%20and%20socioeconomic%20complexities%2C%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20around%20building%20a%20circular%20economy%20around%20coal%20which%20recognises%20that%20a%20coal%20mining%20township%20soon%20becomes%20about%20much%20more%20than%20about%20coal%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20commented.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFinally%2C%20one%20must%20take%20into%20account%20that%20areas%20which%20are%20rich%20in%20coal%20are%20not%20the%20ones%20where%20the%20sun%20shines%20or%20the%20wind%20blows%20in%20abundance%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20implies%20a%20widening%20of%20regional%20imbalances%20as%20a%20result%20of%20mine%20closures.%20All%20this%20necessitates%20a%20more%20broad-based%20bottom-up%20discussion%20around%20energy%20transition%20to%20ensure%20one%20which%20is%20both%20regionally%20balanced%2C%20sustainable%20and%20just.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696951767000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F11124719%2Fezgif.com-gif-maker-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fcoal-india-could-layoff-70000-workers-2050-just-transition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20shows%20that%20a%20just%20and%20sustainable%20transition%20to%20clean%20energy%20will%20be%20crucial%2C%20especially%20for%20specific%20regions%20in%20the%20country%20that%20depend%20heavily%20on%20coal-based%20jobs%2C%20said%20experts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fcoal-india-could-layoff-70000-workers-2050-just-transition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Madhya%20Pradesh%20Official%20Marched%20So%20She%20Could%20Resign.%20The%20Reason%20Is...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20deputy%20collector%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20was%20arrested%20on%20the%20charge%20of%20disrupting%20peace%20after%20her%20foot%20march%20seeking%20%26quot%3Bjustice%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20government%20and%20urging%20it%20to%20accept%20her%20resignation%20as%20she%20wanted%20to%20fight%20the%20upcoming%20assembly%20polls%2C%20reached%20the%20state%20capital%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20foot%20march%2C%20led%20by%20the%20official%2C%20Nisha%20Bangre%2C%20started%20from%20Betul%20district%20on%20September%2028%20and%20reached%20Bhopal%20on%20Monday%20evening.%20She%20was%20arrested%20after%20the%20march%20participants%20started%20proceeding%20towards%20the%20residence%20of%20Chief%20Minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%2C%20a%20police%20official%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMs%20Bangre%2C%20the%20deputy%20collector%20of%20Chhatarpur%20district%2C%20tendered%20her%20resignation%20in%20June%20this%20year.%20But%20it%20has%20not%20been%20accepted%20by%20the%20state%20government%20so%20far%2C%20her%20family%20member%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElections%20to%20the%20230-member%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20assembly%20will%20be%20held%20on%20November%2017%20and%20the%20counting%20of%20votes%20will%20take%20place%20on%20December%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20woman%20official's%20march%20reached%20Bhopal%20on%20Monday%20evening.%20After%20she%20garlanded%20the%20statue%20of%20Dr%20B%20R%20Ambedkar%20and%20started%20marching%20towards%20CM%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan's%20residence%2C%20the%20police%20stopped%20the%20march%20and%20arrested%20her%20for%20violating%20section%20151%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(assembly%20of%20five%20or%20more%20to%20disturb%20peace)%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20Congress%20leader%20said%20that%20when%20Ms%20Bangre%20resisted%20the%20police's%20attempt%20to%20arrest%20her%2C%20her%20dress%20got%20torn.%20Additional%20Police%20Commissioner%20Mahavir%20Singh%20Mujalde%2C%20however%2C%20denied%20the%20claim%2C%20and%20said%20the%20entire%20episode%20was%20captured%20on%20media%20cameras.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20following%20her%20arrest%2C%20Ms%20Bangre%20was%20produced%20in%20a%20local%20court.%20As%20she%20refused%20to%20be%20bailed%20out%2C%20she%20was%20sent%20to%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Bhopal%20Central%20Jail%20official%20Saroj%20Mishra%20said%20that%20Ms%20Bangre%20was%20lodged%20in%20the%20women's%20ward%20inside%20the%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20she%20was%20staging%20a%20hunger%20strike%20inside%20the%20prison%2C%20the%20official%20clarified%20that%20she%20has%20not%20given%20any%20intimation%20in%20writing%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMs%20Bangre%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20(SC)%20category%20resigned%20from%20the%20service%20after%20she%20was%20not%20granted%20leave%20to%20take%20part%20in%20a%20religious%20programme%20in%20her%20hometown%20in%20Betul%20district%2C%20her%20husband%20Suresh%20Agrawal%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20wants%20to%20contest%20the%20assembly%20polls%20from%20Amla%20in%20Betul%20district%2C%20but%20her%20resignation%20has%20not%20been%20accepted%20since%20June%2022%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20nothing%20happened%2C%20she%20embarked%20on%20a%20peaceful%20march%20on%20September%2028%2C%20which%20reached%20Bhopal%20on%20Monday%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20marching%20peacefully%20towards%20the%20chief%20minister's%20residence%2C%20but%20the%20police%20arrested%20her%20midway%20and%20at%20present%20she%20is%20in%20jail%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20informed%20that%20she%20would%20be%20released%20soon%20as%20they%20are%20completing%20necessary%20formalities%20to%20get%20her%20out%20of%20the%20prison.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%