%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NewsClick%20Case%3A%20Purkayastha%2C%20Chakravarti%20Remanded%20to%2010%20Days%20of%20Judicial%20Custody%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F10124838%2Fp-house-court.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20founder%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20the%20news%20portal%E2%80%99s%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20were%20sent%20to%20ten%20days%20of%20judicial%20custody%20in%20the%20Delhi%20police%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditional%20sessions%20judge%20Hardeep%20Kaur%20of%20the%20Patiala%20House%20Courts%20passed%20the%20order%20after%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20were%20produced%20in%20court%20after%20the%20five%20days%20of%20police%20custody%20had%20expired%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fnewsclick-founder-arrest-prabir-purkayastha-judicial-custody-chinese-propaganda-uapa-239778%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20Delhi%20police%E2%80%99s%20special%20cell%20in%20a%20terror%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-terror-fir-against-newsclick-names-chinese-firms-xiaomi-vivo-puts-lawyers-in-crosshairs%5C%22%3Ewhich%20claims%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20received%20Chinese%20funding%20to%20criticise%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%20and%20promote%20Chinese%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditional%20public%20prosecutor%20(APP)%20Atul%20Srivastava%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20Delhi%20police%20was%20seeking%20judicial%20custody%20because%20their%20physical%20presence%20is%20not%20required%20at%20this%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Arshdeep%20Singh%20Khurana%2C%20opposing%20the%20grant%20of%20judicial%20custody%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbare%20reading%20of%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20FIR%20would%20show%20that%20there%20is%20no%20criminal%20offence%20made%20out%E2%80%9D%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20case%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnewsclick-case-allegations-uapa-legal-experts%5C%22%3ENewsClick%20Case%3A%20Do%20Allegations%20Justify%20Invoking%20of%20UAPA%3F%20Legal%20Experts%20Weigh%20In.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20allegation%20that%20I%E2%80%99ve%20used%20any%20bomb%20or%20dynamite%20which%20has%20caused%20loss%20of%20death%20and%20property.%20There%20is%20no%20allegation%20that%20I%E2%80%99ve%20used%20any%20criminal%20force%20in%20the%20entire%20FIR.%20There%20is%20no%20act%20of%20kidnapping%2C%20detention%20or%20abduction.%20None%20of%20the%20acts%20attributed%20to%20me%20has%20any%20elements%20of%20Section%2015%20of%20UAPA%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKhurana%20said%20that%20a%20journalist%20cannot%20be%20punished%20for%20criticising%20the%20government%20in%20power.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fnewsclick-arrests-prabir-purkayastha-amit-chakraborty-remanded-judicial-custody-10-days-delhi-court%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20APP%20Srivastava%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9CYour%20purpose%20was%20not%20criticising%20(the%20government)%20but%20propagating%20the%20propaganda%20of%20a%20country%20that%20is%20inimical%20to%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKhurana%20also%20reiterated%20that%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20not%20received%20any%20money%20from%20China%20and%20all%20investment%20came%20through%20banking%20channels%20and%20was%20duly%20reported%20to%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERohit%20Sharma%2C%20appearing%20for%20NewsClick%E2%80%99s%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%2C%20said%20his%20client%E2%80%99s%20name%20is%20not%20mentioned%20in%20the%20FIR%20as%20an%20accused.%20While%20the%20FIR%20says%20Chakravarti%20owns%20shares%20in%20NewsClick%2C%20his%20holdings%20in%20the%20company%20equal%200.1%25%2C%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20%5Ban%5D%20allegation%20there%20is%20money%20coming%20in%20and%20some%20news%20is%20being%20published%20with%20a%20particular%20agenda.%20I%20have%20not%20been%20involved%20in%20any%20publication.%20I%20am%20not%20a%20journalist%2C%20or%20an%20editor%20or%20writer%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chakravarti%E2%80%99s%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20APP%20Srivastava%20said%20that%20the%20police%20had%20already%20satisfied%20the%20court%20during%20the%20time%20of%20police%20remand%20that%20the%20offences%20were%20made%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%20it%20is%20not%20a%20case%20of%20first%20remand.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20first%20remand%2C%20we%20had%20satisfied%20my%20ladyship%20with%20how%20the%20offences%20were%20made%20out%E2%80%A6%20We%20are%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20collecting%20evidence.%20See%20our%20fairness.%20We%20have%20said%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20police%20remand%20as%20of%20now%20and%20will%20ask%20later%20if%20we%20need%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20were%20arrested%20on%20October%203%20and%20were%20remanded%20to%20seven%20days%20of%20police%20custody%20on%20October%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20high%20court%20on%20Monday%20reserved%20its%20order%20in%20the%20pleas%20moved%20by%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-reserves-judgment-on-pleas-challenging-remand-orders-of-newsclick-editor-hr-head%5C%22%3Echallenging%20the%20trial%20court%E2%80%99s%20remand%20order%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1