0facing%20backlash%20on%20social%20media%20over%20alleged%20anti-India%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPakistan%20news%20outlet%20%3Cem%3ESamaa%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20Abbas%20left%20India%20citing%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D.%20The%20ICC%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20Abbas%E2%80%99s%20departure%20from%20India%20was%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%20ICC%20official%20C.%20Rajshekhar%20Rao%20confirmed%20this%20information%20to%20%3Cem%3EArab%20News%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%2035-year-old%20had%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FZAbbasOfficial%2Fstatus%2F1708719707023360331%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20social%20media%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Chumbled%E2%80%9D%20to%20join%20the%20six-week%20World%20Cup%20coverage%20programme.%20In%20the%20same%20post%2C%20she%20mentioned%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20cultural%20similarities%20than%20differences%E2%80%9D%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20media%20reports%20had%20suggested%20that%20her%20exit%20was%20related%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20following%20a%20complaint%20filed%20in%20Delhi%20by%20a%20lawyer.%20The%20complaint%20filed%20by%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer%20Vineet%20Jindal%20October%206%20accused%20Abbas%20of%20posting%20%E2%80%9Cderogatory%E2%80%9D%20tweets%20targeting%20the%20Hindu%20faith%2C%20based%20on%20screenshots%20of%20posts%20made%20by%20an%20account%20with%20her%20name%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDated%20October%204%2C%20the%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20Abbas%20had%20made%20statements%20that%20were%20anti-India%20and%20Hinduphobic.%20Jindal%20reported%20the%20complaint%20to%20the%20Cyber%20Cell%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20via%20X%2C%20requesting%20the%20filing%20of%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20against%20Abbas%20under%20Sections%20153A%2C%20295%2C%20506%2C%20121%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20and%